    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Blankets woven by Chilkat Tlingit communities, usually made of mountain goat wool and cedar bark. Blankets are usually comprised of black, white, yellow, and blue ovoid shapes. figures, and lines. </Note_Text>
